  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="content">
    <header>
      <h2>CSS Grid</h2>
    </header>
    <p>
      CSS Grid is a powerful new* set of specs that make work like this a lot easier. We just need to describe the grid spacing, and set a couple of heights. Then the Grid just handles everything.
    </p>
    <%- code(`/* The phone screen container */
phone {
  /* Nothing needed here. */
}

/* The top portion of the phone */
main {
  /* ‚ú® magic ‚ú® */
  display: grid;

  /* 4 columns, 4 rows */
  grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
  grid-template-rows: repeat(4, 1fr);

  height: 100vw;
  width: 100vw;
  gap: 4vw; /* Space between apps */
  padding: 4vw; /* Space around the edges */
}

/* The dock at the bottom of the screen */
dock {
  /* ‚ú® magic ‚ú® */
  display: grid;

  /* 4 columns */
  grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);

  height: 28vw;
  width: 100vw;
  gap: 4vw; /* Space between apps */
  padding: 4vw; /* Space around the edges */
}

/* Each app square. */
app {
  border-radius: 20%;
  /* We don‚Äôt need to set the height or width.
     The grid handles it */
}`) %>
    <ul>
      <li><%- link("Proof of concept", { href: "/example/grid-iphone/" }) %></li>
